# MiniSense Phase 2 — CTO-Demo Product Plan

## ✅ Final Decisions (All Questions Resolved)

| Q | Decision |
|---|---|
| Dataset | Extend to Jan–May 2026, realistic CSAT arc (72%→68%→74%→59%→39%) with ~200k records |
| Agent graph | Live SVG animation via SSE events — nodes pulse/highlight as agents run |
| API keys | Store in `.env` (primary). Admin UI calls `PUT /api/config` which writes to `.env`. Fallback to `config/config.json` if `.env` not writable |
| About Developer | Jayant Verma, AI/ML Engineer — bio, portfolio (https://jvt.connect-jv-dev.workers.dev/), LinkedIn, GitHub |
| Multi-KB | Real FAISS rebuild per uploaded document. Each KB gets its own `knowledge_bases/{name}/` directory |

---

## Product Repositioning

**From**: "MiniSense Survey Analysis Agent" (assignment tool)  
**To**: **Multi-Agent Customer Intelligence Platform**  

**Tagline**: *Real AI decisions. Full observability. No black boxes.*

The repositioning is intentional: every page exists to answer a question a technical interviewer or CTO would ask. We are not building a dashboard — we are building a **window into how agentic AI reasons**.

---

## Core Design Principle

> Every feature must either (a) run real code, or (b) display real data from the system. No fake metrics, no hardcoded "AI score" widgets. If it says AI generated it, Groq/LLM generated it.

---

## Technology Stack (No Build Step)

| Layer | Technology | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| Frontend shell | Vanilla HTML + CSS + JS | Works as `file://`, no bundler |
| Routing | Hash-based (`#/dashboard`) | Zero dependencies |
| Charts | Chart.js 4 (CDN) | Beautiful, animated, zero config |
| Diagrams | Mermaid.js (CDN) | Renders architecture from markdown |
