## Key Tradeoffs

| Decision | Choice | Why |
|---|---|---|
| No React/Vue | Vanilla JS | No build step, works as `file://`, simpler to read in interview |
| No WebSocket | SSE + polling | SSE is sufficient for one-way agent trace |
| File-based persistence | JSON files | No DB setup, demo-portable, easy to inspect |
| Config in `config.json` | Not env-only | Admin UI can read/write it; .env stays as override |
| localStorage for run history | Not server-side | Keeps backend simple; history is per-device |
| Pre-run eval results | Stored + rerunnable | Shows eval philosophy without requiring a live run every demo |
| Groq as default | User-switchable | Fast, free tier, best for demo latency |

